HEADWORD: ninon
<hw>ni"non</hw> <pr>(n⟦emac⟧"n⟦ocr⟧n; F. n⟦emac⟧*n⟦ocir⟧N")</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F: nickname for proper name <ets>Anne</ets>;
<fu>1910-15</fu>]</ety> <def>A sturdy cloth material of chiffon or
voile, used for the manufacture of dresses and other women's garments,
and for curtains, and drapery. The material may be constructed by either
a plain or a novelty weaving technique.</def> <au>RHUD</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

